---
title: Effects
description: Effects are fire-and-forget side effects that run when facts change. Use them for logging, analytics, DOM updates, and other non-blocking operations.
---

Effects run side effects without blocking the reconciliation loop. {% .lead %}

---

## Basic Effects

Define effects in your module:

```typescript
const userModule = createModule("user", {
  schema: {
    facts: {
      user: t.object<User>().nullable(),
      page: t.string(),
    },
  },

  effects: {
    logPageView: {
      run: (facts) => {
        analytics.track("page_view", { page: facts.page });
      },
    },

    updateTitle: {
      run: (facts) => {
        document.title = facts.user ? `Welcome, ${facts.user.name}` : "Guest";
      },
    },
  },
});
```

---

## Anatomy of an Effect

```typescript
effects: {
  effectName: {
    // Run on every reconciliation
    run: (facts, prev) => void,

    // Or run only when specific facts change
    watch: (facts) => facts.someValue,
    run: (current, prev, facts) => void,
  },
}
```

---

## The `run` Function

Effects receive current facts and previous facts:

```typescript
effects: {
  logChange: {
    run: (facts, prev) => {
      if (prev?.user?.name !== facts.user?.name) {
        console.log(`User changed from ${prev?.user?.name} to ${facts.user?.name}`);
      }
    },
  },
}
```

### First Run

On first run, `prev` is undefined:

```typescript
effects: {
  initialize: {
    run: (facts, prev) => {
      if (!prev) {
        // First run - initialize external systems
        externalService.init(facts.config);
      }
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Watching Specific Facts

Use `watch` to run only when specific values change:

```typescript
effects: {
  onUserChange: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.user,
    run: (user, prevUser, facts) => {
      if (user && !prevUser) {
        analytics.track("user_login", { userId: user.id });
      }
      if (!user && prevUser) {
        analytics.track("user_logout");
      }
    },
  },
}
```

### Watching Multiple Values

Return an object or array to watch multiple values:

```typescript
effects: {
  onCartChange: {
    watch: (facts) => ({
      items: facts.cart.items,
      total: facts.cart.total,
    }),
    run: (current, prev) => {
      if (current.total !== prev?.total) {
        updateCartBadge(current.items.length);
      }
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Effects vs Resolvers

| Effects | Resolvers |
|---------|-----------|
| Fire-and-forget | Await completion |
| Don't block reconciliation | Block until done |
| For side effects | For satisfying requirements |
| Run after constraints settle | Run when requirements raised |
| Can't modify facts | Can modify facts |

```typescript
// Effect - fire and forget
effects: {
  logUser: {
    run: (facts) => console.log(facts.user), // Just logs, doesn't wait
  },
}

// Resolver - modifies state
resolvers: {
  fetchUser: {
    requirement: "FETCH_USER",
    resolve: async (req, ctx) => {
      ctx.facts.user = await api.getUser(req.userId); // Modifies facts
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Common Use Cases

### Analytics

```typescript
effects: {
  trackPageView: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.route,
    run: (route, prevRoute) => {
      analytics.page(route.path);
    },
  },

  trackAction: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.lastAction,
    run: (action) => {
      if (action) {
        analytics.track(action.type, action.payload);
      }
    },
  },
}
```

### DOM Updates

```typescript
effects: {
  updateMetaTags: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.page,
    run: (page) => {
      document.title = page.title;
      document.querySelector('meta[name="description"]')
        ?.setAttribute("content", page.description);
    },
  },

  updateTheme: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.theme,
    run: (theme) => {
      document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", theme);
    },
  },
}
```

### External Sync

```typescript
effects: {
  syncToLocalStorage: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.preferences,
    run: (prefs) => {
      localStorage.setItem("preferences", JSON.stringify(prefs));
    },
  },

  broadcastChange: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.sharedState,
    run: (state) => {
      broadcastChannel.postMessage({ type: "STATE_UPDATE", state });
    },
  },
}
```

### Logging

```typescript
effects: {
  debugLog: {
    run: (facts, prev) => {
      if (process.env.NODE_ENV === "development") {
        console.log("Facts:", facts);
        console.log("Changed from:", prev);
      }
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Cleanup

Effects can return a cleanup function:

```typescript
effects: {
  subscribeToResize: {
    run: (facts) => {
      const handler = () => console.log("resized");
      window.addEventListener("resize", handler);

      // Cleanup runs before next effect call or on unmount
      return () => {
        window.removeEventListener("resize", handler);
      };
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Async Effects

Effects can be async, but they don't block:

```typescript
effects: {
  sendToServer: {
    watch: (facts) => facts.events,
    run: async (events) => {
      // Fire and forget - errors won't block reconciliation
      await api.sendEvents(events).catch(console.error);
    },
  },
}
```

{% callout type="warning" title="Error handling" %}
Errors in effects don't block reconciliation. Always handle errors in async effects.
{% /callout %}

---

## Effect Order

Effects run after all constraints are satisfied:

```
1. Facts change
2. Constraints evaluate
3. Resolvers run
4. Loop until settled
5. Effects run
```

Effects run in definition order.

---

## Accessing Derivations

Effects can access derivations:

```typescript
effects: {
  logStatus: {
    run: (facts, prev, derive) => {
      console.log(`User: ${derive.fullName}, Admin: ${derive.isAdmin}`);
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Best Practices

### Keep Effects Pure (ish)

Effects should have predictable side effects:

```typescript
// Good - predictable side effect
run: (facts) => {
  localStorage.setItem("user", JSON.stringify(facts.user));
}

// Avoid - modifying unrelated state
run: (facts) => {
  globalCounter++;  // Hard to track
  someGlobalState = facts.user;  // Hidden dependency
}
```

### Don't Modify Facts

```typescript
// Bad - modifying facts in effect
run: (facts) => {
  facts.user.lastSeen = Date.now(); // Don't do this!
}

// Good - use a resolver or separate action
```

### Handle Errors

```typescript
effects: {
  syncData: {
    run: async (facts) => {
      try {
        await api.sync(facts.data);
      } catch (error) {
        console.error("Sync failed:", error);
        // Optionally notify error reporting
        errorReporter.capture(error);
      }
    },
  },
}
```

